text:
Hello,

Will it be possible to lock a dnd_section?

I have a template setup currently like this
```&lt;!--
    label: Blog/articles overview
    templateType: blog_listing
    isAvailableForNewContent: true
--&gt;
{% extends "/main-theme/templates/layouts/base.html" %}
{% block body %}

{% dnd_area 'dnd_area' %}

    {% dnd_section %}
        {% dnd_module path="/main-theme/modules/Header" %}
        {% end_dnd_module %}
    {% end_dnd_section %}

    {% dnd_section %}
        {% dnd_module path="/main-theme/modules/blogs" %}
        {% end_dnd_module %}
    {% end_dnd_section %}

     {% dnd_section %}
        {% dnd_module path="/main-theme/modules/cta"%}
        {% end_dnd_module %}
    {% end_dnd_section %}

{% end_dnd_area %}

{% endblock body %}```
Now I like to lock the dnd sections so there can be new ones added and but the module get not be changed of the template. so they can be switched positions but not be edited (only the content)
